beer.beer_description:
We’ve teamed up with our friends at Garston Hops in New Zealand to create 2 IPA’s that show off what their hops, grown at the southernmost commercial hop farm on
the planet, can do.

Kingston Flyer is a West Coast IPA brewed using Garston’s Rakau and Nelson Sauvin hops to create a unique and intense flavour profile full of grapefruit, apricot, peach and passionfruit.

These world class New Zealand hops have a unique expression due to their unique terrier, sitting between mountain ranges at a latitude of ~45°28'9"S, with sheep grazing beneath the bines to keep the weeds at bay and fresh snow kissing the hop flowers during the winter.

Try this alongside Fly Fishin’, a NEIPA brewed with 100% Garston Motueka.
